* 11. scheduler: handoff
.background ./imgs/bg-ll.png

- mechanism for transfering runqueues
- acts on blocked threads

why cant the OS thread hand the runqueue?

    could give up the runqueue unnecessarily


* 11. scheduler: handoff
.background ./imgs/bg-ll.png

*unparks* *a* *thread* or creates it on demand, has no effect on the thread limit:

- limit applies to *threads* *running* *goroutines* only;
- original thread is blocked, another can take its place.

Effect:

- prevents goroutine starvation!

* 11. handoff
.background ./imgs/bg-ll.png

.image ./imgs/t_main_handoff_0.png

Number of CPU cores (N) = number of runqueues = 2.

* 11. handoff
.background ./imgs/bg-ll.png

.image ./imgs/t_main_handoff_1.png _ 700

Number of CPU cores (N) = number of runqueues = 2.

* 11. The scheduler
.background ./imgs/bg-ll.png

Now we have:

- scalability with # of cores;
- threads dont wait for work;
- work is *balanced* with "work-stealing";
- *handoff* prevents starvation from blocked threads;

* 11. The scheduler
.background ./imgs/bg-ll.png

One last problem: 

- Go scheduling points are *cooperative*

This means the program needs to call the scheduler or nothing will happen

    // CPU bound, long running
    func complicatedAlgo(img) {
        // doenst create goroutines
        // doesnt block
        ...
    }

> This can starve the runqueue

We need one more structure

* 12. Solution: Scheduler Preemption
.background ./imgs/bg-ll.png

    It is the Go runtime mechanism by which it temporarily 
    interrupts a running goroutine to allow other goroutines to run

- scheduler implements asynchronous preemption (Go 1.14+);

    > background thread "sysmon" - monitor;
    > detects long-running goroutines and sends signals (SIGURG on Unix);
    > unschedules goroutines running longer than 10ms.

- preempted goroutines go to global runqueue (GRQ);
- lower priority source queue;
- has a lock;

* 12. scheduler structures
.background ./imgs/bg-ll.png

- Local Run Queues (LRN)
- Global Run Queues (GRN)
- Work Stealing
- Work Handoff
- Preemption

* 12. scheduler limitations
.background ./imgs/bg-ll.png

- no priority: FIFO runqueues defining execution
- no strong preemption: 

    > no strong fairness time distribution for goroutines
    > no latency guarantees

- no hardware localization: topology is unknown

